spec: ab3421
version: ">=3.9"
backend: python_module(abc)

docs: https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html

provenance:
  derived_from:
    - "https://docs.python.org/3/library/abc.html"
    - "Test vectors verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13"
  not_derived_from:
    - "CPython source code"
    - "any proprietary source"
  notes:
    - "Wave 675 (ab3421): __hash__, __eq__, __lt__ dict-presence checks for abc module types."
    - "Theme: __hash__/__eq__/__lt__ dict-presence (hash(x), x==y, x<y)."
    - "All values False — abc types are abstract base class machinery with no custom hash/eq/lt defined in their own __dict__."
    - "All values verified with Python 3.14.4 on macOS/Darwin 25.4.0, 2026-04-13."
    - "Classes covered: abc.ABC, abc.ABCMeta, and type(abc.abstractmethod(lambda: None)) — the built-in function type."
    - "Key finding (__hash__): all 3 abc subjects return false for __hash__. hash() delegates to __hash__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. abc.ABC is a pure abstract base class convenience wrapper with no __hash__ in its own __dict__. abc.ABCMeta is a metaclass responsible for abstract method tracking and virtual subclass registration; __hash__ has no role in ABCMeta's responsibilities and is absent from ABCMeta.__dict__. The function type (type(abc.abstractmethod(lambda: None)) is <class 'function'>) does not define __hash__ in its own __dict__ — functions are callables and descriptors; hash(f) uses the default inherited id-based hash from object, not a custom __hash__ entry in the function type's __dict__. Note: wave 653 (ab3091) already confirmed __hash__ is false for all 3 abc subjects."
    - "Key finding (__eq__): all 3 abc subjects return false for __eq__. == delegates to __eq__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. abc.ABC: no __eq__ in its own __dict__; equality falls back to identity comparison. abc.ABCMeta: does not define __eq__ in ABCMeta.__dict__; the metaclass's API surface (__subclasshook__, register(), __abstractmethods__) has no equality comparison component. The function type: functions use identity-based equality by inheritance from object; no __eq__ is defined in the function type's own __dict__. Note: wave 653 (ab3091) already confirmed __eq__ is false for all 3 abc subjects."
    - "Key finding (__lt__): all 3 abc subjects return false for __lt__. < delegates to __lt__ when defined in the class's own __dict__. abc.ABC: no __lt__ in its own __dict__; ordering raises TypeError by default. abc.ABCMeta: does not define __lt__ in ABCMeta.__dict__. The function type: functions define no ordering protocol in their own __dict__; < between two functions raises TypeError at runtime. Note: wave 654 (ab3106) already confirmed __lt__ is false for all 3 abc subjects."
    - "All 9 values in this wave are false — consistent with the all-false pattern from wave 674 (__bool__/__str__/__repr__). This wave rechecks dunders that were first tested individually in waves 653–654, confirming stability of results."
    - "The function type profile across all waves: true only for __get__ (wave 652), __repr__ (wave 655), and __call__ (wave 656). All other dunders tested — including this wave's __hash__, __eq__, and __lt__ (at the dict-contains level) — are false."
    - "abc.ABCMeta has now returned false for every dunder tested across 24 consecutive waves (652–675). Its entire capability is expressed through class-hierarchy machinery — not operator overloading, comparison, or display protocol overrides."
    - "Cross-wave summary for abc subjects:"
    - "  Wave 652 (ab3076): __get__ true for function type; __set__/__delete__ false."
    - "  Wave 653 (ab3091): __hash__/__eq__/__bool__ all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 654 (ab3106): __lt__/__le__/__gt__ all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 655 (ab3121): __ge__ false; __repr__ true for function type only; __str__ false."
    - "  Wave 656 (ab3136): __call__ true for function type only; __len__/__getitem__ false."
    - "  Wave 657 (ab3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 658 (ab3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 659 (ab3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 660 (ab3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 661 (ab3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 662 (ab3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 663 (ab3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 664 (ab3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 665 (ab3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 666 (ab3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 667 (ab3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 668 (ab3316): __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 669 (ab3331): __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 670 (ab3346): __neg__/__pos__/__abs__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 671 (ab3361): __invert__/__floor__/__ceil__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 672 (ab3376): __trunc__/__round__/__index__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 673 (ab3391): __int__/__float__/__complex__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 674 (ab3406): __bool__/__str__/__repr__ — all false for all 3."
    - "  Wave 675 (ab3421): __hash__/__eq__/__lt__ — all false for all 3."
  created_at: "2026-04-13"

error_model: python_exceptions

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __hash__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__hash__')
#
# All 3 abc subjects return false for __hash__.
# hash() delegates to __hash__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# abc.ABC: a plain abstract base class convenience wrapper with no __hash__
#   in its own __dict__. Hashing falls back to inherited id-based hash.
# abc.ABCMeta: a metaclass for abstract method tracking and virtual subclass
#   registration. __hash__ is absent from ABCMeta.__dict__ — the metaclass's
#   API surface (__subclasshook__, register(), __abstractmethods__) has no
#   hashing component.
# type(abc.abstractmethod(lambda: None)) is <class 'function'>:
#   functions do not define __hash__ in their own __dict__. hash(f) uses
#   the default inherited id-based hash from object. Functions are callables
#   and descriptors with no custom __hash__ entry in the function type's
#   __dict__. Wave 653 (ab3091) first confirmed this result.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table ab3421.hash:
  description: "abc types __hash__ dict-presence checks; wave 675"
  kind: python_call_eq
  version: ">=3.9"
  error_model: python_exceptions
  category: dict_contains
  id_prefix: ab3421

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - ["ab3421001", operator.contains, [abc.ABC.__dict__,                                 "__hash__"], false]
    - ["ab3421002", operator.contains, [abc.ABCMeta.__dict__,                             "__hash__"], false]
    - ["ab3421003", operator.contains, [type(abc.abstractmethod(lambda: None)).__dict__,  "__hash__"], false]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __eq__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__eq__')
#
# All 3 abc subjects return false for __eq__.
# == delegates to __eq__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# abc.ABC: no __eq__ in its own __dict__; equality falls back to identity
#   comparison inherited from object. abc.ABC is a pure abstract base class
#   helper with no state of its own beyond what ABCMeta provides.
# abc.ABCMeta: does not define __eq__ in ABCMeta.__dict__. ABCMeta's
#   entire API surface is class-hierarchy machinery — not equality comparison.
#   == applied to ABCMeta instances falls back to inherited identity equality.
# type(abc.abstractmethod(lambda: None)) is <class 'function'>:
#   functions do not define __eq__ in their own __dict__. Function equality
#   is identity-based by inheritance from object. Wave 653 (ab3091) first
#   confirmed this result.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table ab3421.eq:
  description: "abc types __eq__ dict-presence checks; wave 675"
  kind: python_call_eq
  version: ">=3.9"
  error_model: python_exceptions
  category: dict_contains
  id_prefix: ab3421

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - ["ab3421004", operator.contains, [abc.ABC.__dict__,                                 "__eq__"], false]
    - ["ab3421005", operator.contains, [abc.ABCMeta.__dict__,                             "__eq__"], false]
    - ["ab3421006", operator.contains, [type(abc.abstractmethod(lambda: None)).__dict__,  "__eq__"], false]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# __lt__ dict-presence — operator.contains(Cls.__dict__, '__lt__')
#
# All 3 abc subjects return false for __lt__.
# < delegates to __lt__ when defined in the class's own __dict__.
# abc.ABC: no __lt__ in its own __dict__; < raises TypeError by default
#   since object does not define __lt__.
# abc.ABCMeta: does not define __lt__ in ABCMeta.__dict__. The metaclass
#   is focused on abstract method registration and subclass checking, not
#   ordering. Wave 654 (ab3106) first confirmed this result.
# type(abc.abstractmethod(lambda: None)) is <class 'function'>:
#   functions do not define __lt__ in their own __dict__. < between two
#   functions raises TypeError at runtime since object provides no __lt__.
#   Wave 654 (ab3106) first confirmed this result.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

table ab3421.lt:
  description: "abc types __lt__ dict-presence checks; wave 675"
  kind: python_call_eq
  version: ">=3.9"
  error_model: python_exceptions
  category: dict_contains
  id_prefix: ab3421

  columns: [id, function, args, expected]
  rows:
    - ["ab3421007", operator.contains, [abc.ABC.__dict__,                                 "__lt__"], false]
    - ["ab3421008", operator.contains, [abc.ABCMeta.__dict__,                             "__lt__"], false]
    - ["ab3421009", operator.contains, [type(abc.abstractmethod(lambda: None)).__dict__,  "__lt__"], false]

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# combined — __hash__, __eq__, __lt__ across all 3 abc subjects
#
# Covers the full matrix: 3 classes x 3 methods = 9 rows.
# __hash__: false for all 3.
# __eq__: false for all 3.
# __lt__: false for all 3.
# All 9 values are false.
# Continues the all-false pattern from wave 674 (__bool__/__str__/__repr__).
# This wave rechecks dunders first tested in waves 653 (__hash__, __eq__) and
#   654 (__lt__), confirming the results are stable across the full wave run.
# The function type profile across all waves tested:
#   true:  __get__ (652), __repr__ (655), __call__ (656)
#   false: __set__, __delete__, __hash__, __eq__, __bool__, __lt__, __le__, __gt__,
#          __ge__, __str__, __len__, __getitem__, __setitem__, __delitem__,
#          __contains__, __add__, __sub__, __mul__, __truediv__, __floordiv__,
#          __mod__, __pow__, __lshift__, __rshift__, __and__, __or__, __xor__,
#          __radd__, __rsub__, __rmul__, __rtruediv__, __rfloordiv__, __rmod__,
#          __rpow__, __rlshift__, __rrshift__, __rand__, __ror__, __rxor__,
#          __iadd__, __isub__, __imul__, __itruediv__, __ifloordiv__, __imod__,
#          __ipow__, __ilshift__, __irshift__, __iand__, __ior__, __ixor__,
#          __neg__, __pos__, __abs__, __invert__, __floor__, __ceil__,
#          __trunc__, __round__, __index__, __int__, __float__, __complex__,
#          __bool__ (674), __str__ (674), __repr__ (674),
#          __hash__ (675), __eq__ (675), __lt__ (675)
# The function type is tightly scoped to its role as a callable descriptor
#   with a display representation. Only __get__, __repr__, and __call__ are
#   true for the function type in its own __dict__.
# abc.ABCMeta note: ABCMeta has now returned false for every dunder tested
#   across 24 consecutive waves (652–675). Its power lies exclusively in
#   class-hierarchy machinery — not in operator overloading, comparison,
#   hashing, or display protocol overrides of any kind.
# abc.ABC note: ABC is a pure syntactic convenience for declaring abstract
#   base classes. It has no state of its own beyond what ABCMeta provides,
#   and defines no dunder of any kind in its own __dict__ across all tested
#   waves.
# Cross-wave summary for abc subjects:
#   Wave 652 (ab3076): __get__ true for function type; __set__/__delete__ false.
#   Wave 653 (ab3091): __hash__/__eq__/__bool__ all false for all 3.
#   Wave 654 (ab3106): __lt__/__le__/__gt__ all false for all 3.
#   Wave 655 (ab3121): __ge__ false; __repr__ true for function type only; __str__ false.
#   Wave 656 (ab3136): __call__ true for function type only; __len__/__getitem__ false.
#   Wave 657 (ab3151): __setitem__/__delitem__/__contains__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 658 (ab3166): __add__/__sub__/__mul__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 659 (ab3181): __truediv__/__floordiv__/__mod__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 660 (ab3196): __pow__/__lshift__/__rshift__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 661 (ab3211): __and__/__or__/__xor__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 662 (ab3226): __radd__/__rsub__/__rmul__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 663 (ab3241): __rtruediv__/__rfloordiv__/__rmod__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 664 (ab3256): __rpow__/__rlshift__/__rrshift__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 665 (ab3271): __rand__/__ror__/__rxor__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 666 (ab3286): __iadd__/__isub__/__imul__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 667 (ab3301): __itruediv__/__ifloordiv__/__imod__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 668 (ab3316): __ipow__/__ilshift__/__irshift__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 669 (ab3331): __iand__/__ior__/__ixor__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 670 (ab3346): __neg__/__pos__/__abs__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 671 (ab3361): __invert__/__floor__/__ceil__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 672 (ab3376): __trunc__/__round__/__index__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 673 (ab3391): __int__/__float__/__complex__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 674 (ab3406): __bool__/__str__/__repr__ — all false for all 3.
#   Wave 675 (ab3421): __hash__/__eq__/__lt__ — all false for all 3.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

